From de7a5e07989750691e93f65bc8cdf338afc3df9c Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: gregordinary <33880035+gregordinary@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Sat, 18 Jul 2026 22:12:20 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] clk: rockchip: rk3576: report the USB3 OTG reference clock
 rate

CLK_REF_USB3OTG0/1 are plain xin24m gates, but get_rate had no case for
them and returned -ENOENT. The dwc3 core derives the controller's
reference-clock calibration from clk_get_rate() on exactly this clock
and only guards against a zero rate: the error value reads as a huge
rate, the computed period truncates to zero, and dwc3_ref_clk_period()
overwrites the correct silicon calibration in GUCTL.REFCLKPER and
GFLADJ with garbage. Every controller timer then runs an order of
magnitude slow - port resets take ~500 ms instead of ~50 ms, so the
hub reset loop (which re-arms the reset each 200 ms try) never observes
the port enabled, and the controller cannot halt within the 16 ms
usb-stop timeout. Both hosts on the SoC were unusable.

Report 24 MHz and the calibration comes out right.

Signed-off-by: gregordinary <33880035+gregordinary@users.noreply.github.com>
---
 drivers/clk/rockchip/clk_rk3576.c | 12 ++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 12 insertions(+)

diff --git a/drivers/clk/rockchip/clk_rk3576.c b/drivers/clk/rockchip/clk_rk3576.c
index 69d59586..1f257055 100644
--- a/drivers/clk/rockchip/clk_rk3576.c
+++ b/drivers/clk/rockchip/clk_rk3576.c
@@ -2148,6 +2148,18 @@ static ulong rk3576_clk_get_rate(struct clk *clk)
 	case CLK_REF_OSC_MPHY:
 		rate = rk3576_ufs_ref_get_rate(priv, clk->id);
 		break;
+	/*
+	 * Plain xin24m gates. The dwc3 core derives the controller's
+	 * reference-clock calibration (GUCTL.REFCLKPER, GFLADJ) from this
+	 * rate and only guards against 0: an error return here reads as a
+	 * huge rate, computes a zero period, and overwrites the correct
+	 * silicon calibration - after which every controller timer (port
+	 * reset, halt handshake, SOF) runs an order of magnitude slow.
+	 */
+	case CLK_REF_USB3OTG0:
+	case CLK_REF_USB3OTG1:
+		rate = OSC_HZ;
+		break;
 
 	default:
 		return -ENOENT;
-- 
2.43.0

